TEXT -720 224 Left 2 !.tran 0 5E-3 4E-3 uic
TEXT -728 456 Left 2 !.param Rw=1K
TEXT -728 488 Left 2 !.param Cw=3.3nF
TEXT -728 -136 Left 2 ;V3 is a pulse - necessary to get the ossiclation going.  It would not \nbe necessary in a real circuit, but is necessary in a mathematical model due to \nOp Amp modeled too ideal
TEXT -720 648 Left 2 ;Capacitors should be ceramic of COG, NP0 type for stability
TEXT -720 688 Left 2 ;AD8608 x4 Op Amps\nAD8606 x2 Op Amps\nAD8605 x1 Op Amp
TEXT -720 552 Left 2 ;Double diodes in circuit work to limit out to 2x Vd.  On diode condution R5 in parallel with\nR1 to limit gain.  This type of ossicaltor requires a gain of 3 to work.  Without diode circuit\nin feedback the ouput would swing to the rails and be clipped creating harmonics
TEXT -720 424 Left 2 ;F = 1 / (2*PI*Rw*Cw)
TEXT -720 360 Left 2 ;At R = 11K Frequency = 4.384KHz\nAt R = 1K Frequency = 48.22KHz
TEXT -720 304 Left 2 !.four 48.22k V(VO_2)
